# CodeRabbit CLI

CodeRabbit CLI is installed natively on Windows (no WSL required).

## Commands

- Help: `coderabbit -h` or `cr -h`
- Review uncommitted changes (most common): `coderabbit --agent -t uncommitted`
- Auth status: `coderabbit auth status`

## Agent workflow

When asked to review code or after implementing a feature:

1. Run `coderabbit --agent -t uncommitted` (allow 7–30+ minutes for large changes)
2. Parse the structured JSON output from `--agent`
3. Fix critical and high-severity issues; skip nits unless asked
4. Do not run CodeRabbit more than 3 times on the same set of changes

## Notes

- Do not install CodeRabbit as an npm package — use the CLI only
- CodeRabbit also reads project context from `.cursor/rules/` and `AGENTS.md`
- The CodeRabbit VS Code extension handles inline IDE reviews separately
